The color palettes playfully capture the spectrum of internal contemplation.

metadata.name: Subsurface Fractures #58
metadata.description:
This generative token runs a shader that simulates the refraction and dispersion of light as it passes through a procedural crystal with fractures under the surface.

Each token has a unique fracture pattern and several hidden properties that define how the light bounces within the crystal. 

Major styles are defined with features, some styles are rarer than others.

This token is GPU intensive, viewing on desktop is recommended.

Press ‚ÄúP‚Äù to pause rotation.
Press ‚ÄúUP‚Äù or ‚ÄúDOWN‚Äù to increase or decrease the number of simulated rays per pixel, this will have an impact on performance.

metadata.name: Subatomic Compositions #424
metadata.description:
My love of physics predates my love for generative systems. This piece explores the compositional beauty that can arise from particle collisions in the subatomic space. The aesthetic is based on bubble chamber photography: the paths of particles are traced and photographed as they split and collide.

The primary particle travels at extreme speeds, looping around until it collides with another particle. The resulting explosion is traced out and interesting events are highlighted. Some of the particles shoot off at incredible velocity, and others spiral tighter and tighter until they blink out of existence.

This is a study in composition.

metadata.name: Sand Table #91
metadata.description:
Just like a sand jar that you made or played with as a child. A recreation of layered colored sand with star glitter at the "peaks." Rare versions will be all gold and super rare has rainbow shimmer glitter.

Press 's' to take a screenshot. The image size is 1000x1000. 

Features
- 20 color palettes
- 2 color distribution methods
- 4 sand distribution methods
- sand size variation
- noise variables to determine patterns and layers

Rare features
- color sand with gold stars
- all stars instead of sand grains
- all gold glitter with silver stars
- all rainbow glitter with silver stars (super rare)

metadata.name: Tympanic #19
metadata.description:
Tympanic is a companion piece to Euphonic [https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/10982] and is released as a free gift to all collectors of Euphonic.

Like Euphonic, this piece attempts to play with the idea of interference and emergent patterns, but this time does so by using pixelation instead of Moire. In this way, where Euphonic was about emergent melodies, Tympanic is about emergent rhythms.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.
